      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "message": "Create a summary of Jira tasks with the following details:\n\n1. **New tasks assigned to me in the last 48 hours**\n2. **Tasks assigned to me that are overdue**\n3. **Tasks assigned to other people that are overdue**\n4. **Tasks that were completed in the last 48 hours**\n5. **New tasks created in the last 48 hours (regardless of assignee)**\n\nUse the Jira API to fetch the data. Credentials are stored in `/home/lstopar/.openclaw/.env`.\n\n### Linking\n\n**Every task, epic, and story key mentioned in the summary MUST be a clickable link.**\n\nFormat: `[KEY-123](https://edgetech-atlassian.atlassian.net/browse/KEY-123)`\n\nFor example:\n- Instead of `PROJ-42`, write `[PROJ-42](https://edgetech-atlassian.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-42)`\n- This applies to ALL issue keys — tasks, stories, epics, subtasks, bugs, etc.\n- If a task belongs to an epic, show the epic as a linked key too, e.g.: `Epic: [PROJ-10](https://edgetech-atlassian.atlassian.net/browse/PROJ-10)`\n\nAfter completing the task, respond with:\n- A **success/failure indicator** (e.g., `✅ Success` or `❌ Failed`).\n- A **1-5 bullet-point summary** of what was accomplished. For example:\n  - Found **3 new tasks** assigned to you.\n  - **2 tasks** are overdue.\n  - **5 tasks** were completed in the last 48 hours.\n\n**Important**: Use the `message` tool to post the result to Telegram topic `987` (`#ops @edgetech`) in chat `8403014547`. Example:\n```json\n{\n  \"action\": \"send\",\n  \"to\": \"8403014547\",\n  \"message\": \"Your result here\",\n  \"threadId\": \"987\"\n}\n```\n\nFormat the response for Telegram.",
