    {
      "id": "8d36ec52-0c10-4376-bd85-44d358abed6c",
      "agentId": "lstopar-agent",
      "name": "Nightly Personal Gmail Triage",
      "enabled": true,
      "createdAtMs": 1771618729376,
      "updatedAtMs": 1773288439301,
      "schedule": {
        "kind": "cron",
        "expr": "0 5 * * *",
        "tz": "Europe/Ljubljana"
      },
      "sessionTarget": "isolated",
      "wakeMode": "now",
      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "thinking": "off",
        "message": "### Gmail Triage Agent\n\n#### Tooling\n- **gogcli** (Google Workspace CLI): `/workspace/.npm-global/bin/gogcli`\n- Account: `luka@stopar.si`\n\n#### Step 1 — Fetch emails\n```bash\n/workspace/.npm-global/bin/gogcli gmail search 'newer_than:27h in:inbox' --max 200 --account luka@stopar.si --json\n```\nOutputs JSON with a `threads` array. If empty, post \"📬 Gmail Triage — inbox clear.\" to Telegram topic 1299 and stop.\n\n#### Step 2 — Skip already-processed\nCheck semantic memory for each `thread.id` under key `gmail_triage:<id>`. Skip threads already stored.\n\n#### Step 3 — Classify each email\nUse the `llm-task` tool to classify all unprocessed emails in a single call. Return a JSON array:\n```json\n[{\"id\": \"...\", \"threadId\": \"...\", \"subject\": \"...\", \"sender\": \"...\", \"category\": \"...\"}]\n```\nCategories (pick exactly one): `Actionable` | `Informational` | `Updates` | `LinkedIn` | `Promotions` | `Invoices` | `Trading212` | `Qogita` | `GoogleWorkspace` | `Google` | `Apple` | `Bitstamp` | `Wise` | `GitHub` | `Revolut` | `Forums` | `Calendar`\n\n#### Step 4 — Actions per category\n\n**Auto-archive** (run for each): `Updates`, `LinkedIn`, `GitHub`, `Revolut`, `Informational`, `Promotions`, `GoogleWorkspace`, `Google`, `Apple`, `Bitstamp`, `Wise`, `Forums`\n```bash\n/workspace/.npm-global/bin/gogcli gmail thread modify <threadId> --remove INBOX --account luka@stopar.si --json\n```\nIf a thread fails to archive, skip it and note the error in the summary.\n\n**Promotions** — also attempt HTTP GET on `List-Unsubscribe` header URL before archiving.\n\n**Invoices** — download PDF attachment, upload to Google Drive:\n- MineIT invoices → folder `1XjBZZeHvkxJedw6SBDLhFdCwXmOjfzv7`, subfolder `yyyy-MM`\n- Other invoices → folder `1GPfmza6HbnWlfO4TyQw16XXNWHZxK2HC`, subfolder `yyyy-MM`\n\n**Calendar/Zoom** — extract event details and create Google Calendar event via gogcli, then archive.\n\n**Actionable** — do NOT archive. Draft a reply if you have enough context (search memory + Confluence first). Leave in inbox.\n\n**Trading212** / **Qogita** — keep in inbox, do not archive.\n\n#### Step 5 — Memory\nFor each processed thread, store in memory under key `gmail_triage:<threadId>`:\n- subject, sender, category, action taken, timestamp\n\n#### Step 6 — Telegram summary\nPost to topic `1299` in chat `8403014547`:\n```json\n{\"action\": \"send\", \"to\": \"8403014547\", \"threadId\": \"1299\", \"message\": \"<summary>\"}\n```\n\nFormat — group by category, include Gmail links:\n```\n📬 Gmail Triage — {date} {time}\n📊 {total} processed | 🗂 {archived} archived | ✉️ {drafts} drafts\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n✉️ Actionable ({n})\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n• [Subject](https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/#inbox/{threadId}) — 1-2 sentence summary\n\n[other categories...]\n```\n- Archived categories: use `#all/{threadId}` link\n- Inbox categories: use `#inbox/{threadId}` link\n- Only show categories with ≥1 email\n- Max 10 per category, then \"… and N more\"\n```"
      },
