      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "message": "You are Darwin, the knowledge graph curator. Run your nightly fact extraction and curation now.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Load last run state\n\nRead `/workspace/last-scan.json`. It contains `lastRunAt` (ISO timestamp or null). If null, this is your first run — scan everything from the last 7 days.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Discover active sessions\n\nCall `sessions_list(activeMinutes=1440)` to get all sessions active in the last 24h.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Extract new facts from session history\n\nFor each session:\n1. Call `sessions_history(sessionKey=\"...\", limit=200)` to get recent messages\n2. **Filter to only messages with `timestamp > lastRunAt`** — skip anything already processed\n3. If no new messages, skip this session entirely\n4. Read through new messages and extract FACTUAL statements about things that already exist or have happened\n\nSKIP: plans/proposals (\"we should\", \"let's build\"), greetings, questions without confirmed answers, future intentions.\n\nEXTRACT: people + roles/relationships, technologies confirmed in use, decisions made, configurations confirmed in place.\n\n**Deduplicate before every insert:**\n1. `knowledge_graph(action=\"entity\", entity=\"<subject>\")` — check if subject exists\n2. If the exact `relation + object` is already stored → skip\n3. Otherwise → `knowledge_graph(action=\"add\", ...)`\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — Verify existing facts (Strategy #1: session cross-reference)\n\nSample up to 30 facts from the knowledge graph using `knowledge_graph(action=\"recent\", limit=30)`.\n\nFor each fact, check: does the session history actually support this? Use `memory_search` to find corroborating evidence.\n\nSpecifically:\n- For each fact, run `memory_search(query=\"<subject> <relation> <object>\", maxResults=3)`\n- If the search returns **no supporting evidence at all** (score < 0.5 on all results), flag the fact as unverified\n- If a memory result **directly contradicts** the fact (e.g. fact says A works_at X, but memory says A works_at Y), mark it for removal\n\nFor facts marked for removal: log them and remove them from the KG (use `knowledge_graph(action=\"add\")` is not suitable for deletion — note unverifiable facts in the run log for manual review instead, as the KG tool may not support deletion directly).\n\nCollect a list of unverified/contradicted facts to include in the report.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5 — Contradiction detection (Strategy #2)\n\nFor each entity found during extraction (plus a sample of up to 20 existing entities from `knowledge_graph(action=\"recent\")`), check for internal contradictions:\n\n1. Fetch all facts for the entity: `knowledge_graph(action=\"entity\", entity=\"<name>\")`\n2. Look for conflicting relation pairs — same relation type, different objects — e.g.:\n   - Two different `works_at` values\n   - Two different `located_at` values\n   - Two different `has_role` values where only one can be true\n3. For each contradiction found:\n   - Use `memory_search` to determine which version is more recently supported\n   - Flag the older/less-supported version\n   - Log the contradiction for the report\n\nNote: if the KG tool does not support deletion, log contradictions clearly so they can be resolved manually or on next iteration.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6 — Save state\n\nWrite back `/workspace/last-scan.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"lastRunAt\": \"<current ISO timestamp>\",\n  \"lastRunSummary\": {\n    \"sessionsScanned\": N,\n    \"factsAdded\": N,\n    \"factsSkipped\": N,\n    \"factsUnverified\": N,\n    \"contradictionsFound\": N\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAlso write a brief log to `/workspace/memory/<YYYY-MM-DD>.md` including any flagged facts.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7 — Report\n\nSummarise in 5–8 lines:\n- Sessions scanned, facts added, facts skipped (duplicates)\n- Facts flagged as unverified (list them briefly)\n- Contradictions detected (list entity + conflicting values)\n- Any facts removed or marked for manual review",
